   "battle": "Bring a bow and as many arrows as you can spare — ancient arrows are the real answer here, with bomb arrows as backup — plus a sturdy shield to parry, and eat an attack-up or defense-up dish first; if you've got the Master Sword, it deals extra damage to Guardians for the finish. The fight opens with this flying Guardian sweeping a red searchlight; the moment it spots you it locks on and charges a blue laser from above, so keep moving. The core loop is to target its glowing eye: a well-aimed arrow to the eye staggers it and interrupts the attack, and a clean ancient-arrow hit to the eye can destroy it outright. If it's hard to aim, use Stasis to freeze it for about two seconds, or fire while gliding off an updraft to drop into slow-motion. As a safe fallback, raise your shield and parry the laser right as it fires to bounce the beam back — it takes a few clean parries. You can also knock it out of the sky by blasting its propellers (a few bomb arrows each, or one ancient arrow per propeller); once they're all destroyed it crashes down defenseless for an easy melee finish. Your reward is a haul of valuable ancient parts — gears, screws, shafts, springs, and Ancient Cores — and, if you're lucky, the rare Giant Ancient Core used for the best upgrades."
