   "drops": "Ancient parts (often Ancient Screw/Spring)",
   "battle": "Bring a sturdy shield you don't mind scratching, a bow with a stack of arrows, and a defense-up dish (a Tough meal from armored fish or rugged ingredients) so a stray laser won't one-shot you; Ancient armor helps a lot if you have it, and the Master Sword (like all ancient weapons) hits harder against these corrupted machines. A Decayed Guardian is a broken husk half-buried in the ground — it has no legs and cannot move or chase you, so the only thing it does is lock its glowing eye onto you and fire a laser. The fight starts the moment its eye lights up and a thin targeting line finds you, so don't panic: you have a moment before it shoots. The clean win is to raise your shield and tap A to parry the beam right as it fires (a hair late beats early) — the laser bounces back into its own eye and a single perfect deflect destroys it outright. If parrying scares you, just shoot it: an arrow to the eye stuns it, and one Ancient Arrow to the eye blows it up instantly. The easy fallback is to keep your distance behind a rock and chip away, or use Stasis to freeze it while you reposition — since it can't follow you, you're never truly in danger. It drops valuable Ancient parts (Ancient Screws, Springs, Gears, and Shafts) you'll want for buying Ancient gear and arrows later."
