   "battle": "Bring your strongest weapon, a bow with a good stack of arrows, and a sturdy shield, plus a meal that boosts attack or defense (or restores a lot of hearts) — these hit very hard, so a hearty or armor-up dish gives you breathing room. The fight starts when the Blademaster appears in a puff and goes invisible or teleports around with its big two-handed windcleaver; stay patient and keep your eyes on it. The core loop: when it leaps up for the heavy overhead slam, wait for it to commit, then dodge to the side at the last instant to trigger a flurry rush and unload, or shoot an arrow at its head to stagger it and rush in for free hits — repeat until it drops. When it cracks the ground and a gust kicks up, pop your paraglider in the updraft, float above, and strike down from the air. The easy fallback: stay hidden and toss a Mighty Banana on the ground — it can't resist, and while it's distracted you sneak up for a one-hit sneakstrike (Ancient Arrows also obliterate them from range). One catch: beat it in fair combat — a stealth kill or keeping it stunned the whole time means no weapon — and it can drop its Windcleaver, a strong swift blade, along with Mighty Bananas and gems."
