   "battle": "The Red-maned Lynel is the weakest kind, so it's the best one to learn on — but it still hits hard, so come prepared. Bring a strong weapon, a bow with plenty of arrows, a sturdy shield for parrying, and a meal that boosts attack or defense before you start. Sneak in close first, since Lynels hear you from a long way off. Open with an arrow to its head — a clean headshot makes it stagger and kneel, so sprint in, press up to mount its back, and mash attack for big free damage that doesn't even wear out your weapon. After you're thrown off, run the core loop: bait its melee swing and hop aside at the last instant for a flurry rush, or raise your shield as it swings to parry. Stay right on top of it so it can't back off to breathe fire or fire shock arrows from range; when it plants its weapon to blast fire, dash or circle away from the blast. Every headshot stuns it again — remount and repeat. If the fight overwhelms you, lean on Urbosa's Fury or Stasis to freeze it for free hits, and keep food ready to heal. Its drops — Lynel horns, hooves, and guts, plus its powerful sword, bow, and shield — are some of the best in the game."
